The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Friday, August 13, 2004 				 Crack team for arrears
 OUR CORRESPONDENT				 	 Chidambaram: Hard talk																								New Delhi, Aug. 12: The finance ministry today formed two task forces to help recover the shortfall in taxes and help bridge the countrys gaping fiscal deficit.																								Of the Rs 87,000-crore shortfall, including both direct and indirect taxes, about Rs 7,000-8,000 crore is easily recoverable and the finance minister, P. Chidambaram plans to discuss the matter with the Chief Justice of India and high courts for a speedier decision on tax dispute cases.The task force on direct taxes will be headed by member (revenue). The chief commissioner (tax arrears and recovery) will head the body on indirect tax collection, said a finance ministry statement. The task forces, which start functioning from today, will report to the respective boards.																								Chidambaram wants to put in place a procedure at the chief commissioners and income tax appellate tribunal levels that will help him collect about Rs 7,000-8,000 crore this year. 
